 respectively. We further find that the power\nspectrum of density fluctuations, $P(\\rho_k/\\left<\\rho\\right>)$, increases in\nmagnitude with increasing $\\mathrm{Ri}$, whereas the velocity power spectrum is\ninvariant. Thus, the ratio between density and velocity power spectra strongly\ndepends on $\\mathrm{Ri}$. Pressure fluctuations, on the other hand, are\nindependent of stratification and only depend on $\\mathcal{M}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Jan 2020 19:00:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Mar 2020 01:02:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 25 Mar 2020 06:27:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-26"}
